# Nmap Basics

## What is Nmap?
Nmap (Network Mapper) is an open-source tool used for network scanning and security auditing.

## Why Nmap is important in cybersecurity
- Used for discovering live hosts
- Identifies open ports on a system
- Detects running services and versions
- Helps in vulnerability assessment

## Common uses of Nmap
- Network mapping
- Port scanning
- Service detection
- OS fingerprinting

## Basic Nmap commands

### Scan a target
nmap 192.168.1.1

### Scan a website
nmap example.com

### Scan multiple ports
nmap -p 80,443 example.com

### Fast scan
nmap -F example.com

## Note
Nmap should only be used on systems you own or have permission to scan.
